TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jaud, Melise
AU  - Kukenova, Madina
AU  - Strieborny, Martin
T1  - Finance, Comparative Advantage, and Resource Allocation*
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfx047
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 22
IS  - 3
SP  - 1011
EP  - 1061
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Can financial institutions and markets enhance the discipline imposed by competitive product markets and thus improve resource allocation in the real economy? We address this question in the context of international trade, using disaggregated product-level data from seventy-one countries exporting to the USA. We show that exported products exit the US market sooner if they stand far away from the exporting country’s comparative advantage. This pattern is stronger when the exporting country has a well-developed banking system, but it is unaffected by the depth of stock markets. These results are in accordance with theories stressing the disciplining role of debt and monitoring abilities of banks.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfx047
ER  - 



