TY  - JOUR
AU  - El Ghoul, Sadok
AU  - Guedhami, Omrane
AU  - Kwok, Chuck
AU  - Zheng, Xiaolan
T1  - Zero-Leverage Puzzle: An International Comparison*
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfw065
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 22
IS  - 3
SP  - 1063
EP  - 1120
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Using a large sample of firms from developed and developing countries over the 1990–2010 period, we document evidence of zero-leverage firms around the world. Further, we find strong and robust evidence that in countries with high scores on Schwartz’s Conservatism and Mastery indices as well as high levels of trust, firms are more likely to employ a zero-leverage policy, after controlling for various firm- and country-level determinants of leverage. Finally, we find that firms with zero leverage have a lower cost of equity capital in countries where a zero-leverage policy is more compatible with the local culture.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfw065
ER  - 



